# Global Conventions & Documentation

## Language

- **Generated documents** (docs, comments in code, README, ADRs): use **English**.
- **Chat replies**: use **Russian** or **English** depending on the user's prompt language.

## Repository

- Project: **WalletRadar** — https://github.com/Volad/wallet-radar

## Documentation Structure

### Global wiki (authoritative reference)

Start at [`docs/README.md`](docs/README.md).

| Area | Path | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| Overview | `docs/overview/` | Product context, domain, architecture, data model, orchestration |
| Pipeline | `docs/pipeline/` | Backfill, normalization, linking, pricing, cost basis, replay, portfolio snapshot |
| Normalization rules | `docs/pipeline/normalization/rules/` | Families, protocols, three-layer contract |
| Frontend | `docs/frontend/` | Dashboard, move basis, settings, lending UI |
| Reference | `docs/reference/` | API, glossary, networks/protocols, transaction types, ledger/basis effects |
| Examples | `docs/examples/` | Synthetic walkthroughs (no real tx hashes) |

### Current work (separate from wiki linear reading order)

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/adr/*.md` | Architecture Decision Records — **one ADR per file**; explain **why** and **when** |
| `docs/tasks/` | Implementation plans, cycle closeouts, audit artifacts |

When creating or updating docs, place content in the correct wiki file. Keep ADRs and tasks separate from the global wiki. Keep ADRs focused (one decision, one file).
